d^n(x^n)/dx^n = n!
d^{n+1}(x^{n+1}) / dx^{n+1} =  d^n \left(\frac{d(x^{n+1})} {dx}\right) /dx^n 
n=1
n=0
n>1
n-1
\dfrac{d^1}{dx^1}x^1 = \dfrac{d}{dx}x = 1 = 1! 
\dfrac{d^n}{dx^n}x^n = \dfrac{d^{n-1}}{dx^{n-1}} \lbrace \dfrac{d}{dx}x^n \rbrace = \dfrac{d^{n-1}}{dx^{n-1}} \lbrace nx^{n-1} \rbrace 
 =n(n-1)!=n! 
f_{n} = x^{n}
f_{0} = 1
\dfrac{d^1}{dx^1}f_{n} = nf_{n-1}
\dfrac{d^2}{dx^2}f_{n} = n(n-1)f_{n-2}
\dfrac{d^n}{dx^n}f_{n} = n(n-1)(n-2)(n-3)...(n-(n-1))f_{0}
k = n + 1
\dfrac{d^{k}}{dx^{k}}f_{k} = (n+1)n\dfrac{d^{k-1}}{dx^{k-1}}f_{n} = k!
